                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13501719" author="komusubi" created="Wed, 21 Nov 2012 06:23:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;modify simple project from maven quick start.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13501910" author="svenmeier" created="Wed, 21 Nov 2012 12:18:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Problem is that in WicketFilter#init() the application is created before the contextClassLoader is set, thus HomePage.class isn&apos;t loaded via the custom classLoader.&lt;br/&gt;
Later MarkupResourceStream#getMarkupClass() resolves classes via WicketObjects, which uses the custom classLoader via contextClassLoader set in WicketFilter#processRequest().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13502122" author="svenmeier" created="Wed, 21 Nov 2012 16:55:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After fixing the thread&apos;s contextClassLoader I stumbled into further problems, e.g. the application&apos;s name can&apos;t be set again.&lt;br/&gt;
It seems we have to properly destroy the old application to make sure everything is reloaded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which version of Wicket did this work for you?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13502392" author="svenmeier" created="Wed, 21 Nov 2012 22:48:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The contextClassLoader is now set before creating application and the application is properly destroyed before initializing the new on&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13502663" author="komusubi" created="Thu, 22 Nov 2012 09:06:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks svenmeier.&lt;br/&gt;
i confirmed  branch on master and 1.5.x. it cleared this problem completely !&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i looking for next release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
